Summary: This solution contains 'knockout-fadeVisible' and 'knockout-slideDownVisible' which are extensions for knockout.js (http://knockoutjs.com/)
Author: martin kramer <martin.kramer@lostindetails.com>
License: MIT

Dependencies:
  1) jQuery.js (http://jquery.com)
  2) knockout.js (http://knockoutjs.com)

Usage:
  1) Include jquery and knockout on your page first, then include knockout-fadeVisible.min.js and/or knockout-slideDownVisible.min.js
     e.g.:
    <script type="text/javascript" src="Scripts/jquery-2.2.1.min.js"></script>
    <script type="text/javascript" src="Scripts/knockout-3.4.0.js"></script>
    <script type="text/javascript" src="Scripts/knockout-fadeVisible.min.js"></script>
    <script type="text/javascript" src="Scripts/knockout-slideDownVisible.min.js"></script>
   
  2) Use the binding 'fadeVisible' or 'slideDownVisible' instead of 'visible' (http://knockoutjs.com/documentation/visible-binding.html)
     e.g.:
     <div class="panel-body" data-bind="fadeVisible: isVisible">...
     or <div class="panel-body" data-bind="slideDownVisible: isVisible">...

Example Usage:
  Take a look at ./ko-bindings/index.html
